# Daily Report Operations Rule

## Objective
- Maintain one professional report file per day in `vedant/Daily report/`.
- Capture what was changed, what was completed, what issues were faced, and next actions.

## Daily File Rule
- At session start, derive today's date in `YYYY-MM-DD`.
- Use report file path: `vedant/Daily report/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.
- If the file does not exist, create it immediately on Monday-Friday.
- On Saturday-Sunday, only create the file if explicitly requested.

## Required Daily Sections
- Report metadata (date, owner, status).
- Executive summary (business-focused, concise).
- Priorities worked on (with impact, estimate, deadline, owner, status).
- What I changed (professional list of concrete updates).
- Work completed (outcomes delivered).
- Issues faced (problem, impact, severity, status).
- Resolutions and mitigations (how issues were handled).
- Blockers and escalations (owner and next action).
- Decisions made (important trade-offs or approvals).
- Backlog delta (added/removed/reprioritized).
- Metrics snapshot (completed, in-progress, blocked counts).
- End-of-day close (done, not done, carry-forward, tomorrow first task).

## Writing Standard
- Keep tone professional and audit-friendly.
- Prefer measurable outcomes over vague statements.
- Every blocker must include an escalation action and owner if unresolved.
- Use statuses only: `todo`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `done`, `dropped`.

